50|$|Black, {{manganese}} oxides with a dendritic crystal habit often found on fracture or rock surfaces are often {{assumed to be}} <b>pyrolusite</b> although careful analyses of numerous examples of these dendrites has shown {{that none of them}} are in fact <b>pyrolusite.</b> Instead, they are other forms of manganese oxide.|$|E
