5000|$|Baddeleyite {{belongs to}} the oxide group, having a {{composition}} of ZrO2. Similar minerals belonging to the same group are the rutile group: rutile (TiO2), <b>pyrolusite</b> (MnO2), cassiterite (SnO2), uraninite (UO2) and thorianite (ThO2). Baddeleyite is chemically homogeneous, but it may contain impurities such as Ti, Hf, and Fe. [...] Higher concentrations of Ti and Fe are restricted to mafic-ultramafic rocks.|$|E
